Interface Plugin

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Comparable<Plugin>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ActionHandler, Executable, ResourceIndexer
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractActionHandler, AbstractExecutable, AbstractPlugin, AbstractResourceIndexer, FileTypeResourceIndexer, ImportIndexer, OsgiManifestBundleIndexer, PriorityActionHandler
    public interface Plugin
extends Comparable<Plugin>
    Common plugin interface. Every plugin must implement it.
    Author:
    Jiri Kucera (jiri.kucera@kalwi.eu)

      • CFG_PRIORITY

        static final String CFG_PRIORITY
        Configuration property name for plugin priority.

        The value must be an integer or PRIORITY_MAX_VALUE and PRIORITY_MIN_VALUE constants.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • CFG_KEYWORDS

        static final String CFG_KEYWORDS
        Configuration property name for plugin keywords.

        The value must be a string or list of strings separated by comma.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • CFG_DESCRIPTION

        static final String CFG_DESCRIPTION

      • getPluginKeywords

        @Nonnull
List<String> getPluginKeywords()
        Returns an optional array of plugin keywords or zero-length array if no keyword is specified.

        Keywords can be used to more precise specifying of plugin(s) returned by PluginManager.

        Returns:
        an array of keywords.
